# gjoa-patch:
#   baseline-firefox: 152.0.1
#   touches:
#     - servo/components/style/values/specified/color.rs
#     - servo/components/style/device/gecko.rs
#     - layout/base/nsPresContext.h
#     - layout/base/nsPresContext.cpp
#     - layout/base/PresShell.cpp
#     - dom/chrome-webidl/BrowsingContext.webidl
#     - docshell/base/BrowsingContext.h
#     - docshell/base/BrowsingContext.cpp
#   depends-on:
#     - rust-path crate::computed_value_flags::ComputedValueFlags
#
Engine-level dark mode: luminance-invert resolved absolute colors at
style-resolution time (the performant successor to the compositor filter:invert).

- specified/color.rs: invert_color_luminance() compresses lightness in OKLCH
  (perceptually uniform, the same space as the 0013 text retone) — NOT a full
  WCAG flip. The page's OKLCH L in [0,1] is mapped linearly onto a comfortable
  band [floor, ceiling]: white (L=1) -> floor (a comfortable dark, ~#161616, NOT
  black — the old target=1-luminance flip is what made content too dark) and
  black (L=0) -> ceiling (~#e4e4e4, NOT pure white). Only L moves; OKLCH chroma
  and hue are carried through untouched, and alpha is preserved. floor/ceiling are
  the live prefs gjoa.darkmode.invert.bgLightness / fgLightness (0-100 percent ==
  OKLCH L*100), read by Device::color_inversion_floor/ceiling. Applied at the END
  of Color::to_computed_color so it covers EVERY resolved absolute color — explicit
  colors, resolved color-functions, AND system colors (so the page Canvas/default
  background goes dark under force-light, not just explicit colors). currentColor /
  color-mix / unresolved color-functions stay symbolic and resolve against the
  already-inverted values. Cached in ComputedValues -> zero per-frame cost; raster
  media untouched.
- device/gecko.rs: color_inversion() accessor (mirrors forced_colors()) +
  color_inversion_floor()/color_inversion_ceiling() reading the cached band.
- nsPresContext.{h,cpp}: per-document mColorInversion flag + mColorInversionFloorL
  /mColorInversionCeilL band + UpdateColorInversion (content-only; chrome
  excluded), called at construction and on change of the
  gjoa.darkmode.invert.{enabled,bgLightness,fgLightness} prefs (live toggle +
  live "Darkness" re-tone via RecascadeSubtree).

The "engine" dark-mode mode (src/gjoa chrome) forces prefers-color-scheme:light
then flips this flag, so sites render light and the engine inverts to dark.

Dark-mode-v2 Tier b (no flash-of-light in the per-site "hybrid" mode):
- nsPresContext: mHybridDefaultInvert + ApplyHybridDefaultInvertIfThemeless().
  In hybrid mode a top document starts UN-inverted, so its first cascade exposes
  the page's AUTHORED background. PresShell::Initialize then reads that root
  background (un-inverted = accurate) and, for a themeless page (light or
  transparent), flips the whole document to inverted BEFORE first paint — so it
  renders dark with no flash. A page that authored its own dark theme is left
  native. Gated on pref gjoa.darkmode.hybrid.default-invert.
- DefaultBackgroundColor(): when inverting a light-scheme document, the canvas /
  inter-page backstop is compressed with the SAME OKLCH-L mapping (neutral color,
  so OKLCH L == cbrt(WCAG luminance)), so the backstop is the same comfortable
  dark as the page — no white frame flashes between navigations or behind
  suppressed paints, and no black frame either.
- PresShell.cpp: the one call site (ApplyHybridDefaultInvertIfThemeless), placed
  after the root frame is built and before painting is unsuppressed.
